desc:
Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Increases armor by %s;
Increases armor resistance by %s;
Increases hull integrity by %s;
Reduces maximum speed by %s;
Decreases mobility by %s.

Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Increases the maximum speed of the ship by %s;
Increases the high-explosive damage received by the ship's hull/armor by %s, reducing the armor by %s points.

Built-in modular system; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod. On activation, has the following effect:

Ballistic weapon firing rate increased by %s;
Ballistic and missile weapon ammo recovery rate increased by %s;
Ballistic weapon flux cost reduced by %s.

Built-in modular system; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Increases hull integrity by %s;
Decreases armor by %s;
When not firing, repairs %s of existing hull integrity per second and reduces the repair time of weapons and engines by %s;
Limits the maximum hull integrity that can be repaired in a single combat (by all hullmods with a repair effect) to %s. This hullmod can only repair up to %s hull integrity in a single combat.

On activation, has the following effect:
Disables weapons and shields, and for a short duration, reduces all incoming damage by %s.

Built-in modular system; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Reduces hull integrity by %s;
Adds two fighter bays;
Reduces the fighter replacement rate reduction by %s;
Increase combat range of fighters by %s. This range bonus is reduced as flux level increases.
All LPCs not created by this ship system will immediately be destroyed.

On activation, has the following effect:
Immediately replenish lost strikecrafts.

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to a strike wings;
Reduce the Austenite's actual engine speed by %s .

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to assault wings;
Reduce the damage of all weapons on the Austenite - class by %s.

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to a support wings;
Reduce base range of all weapons on the Austenite - class by %s .

Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Reduces armor by %s;
Reduces hull integrity by %s;
Increases flux capacity by %s;
Increases flux dissipation by %s;
Activates zero-flux acceleration bonus while below %s flux.

Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Increases hull integrity by %s
Increases EMP resistance by %s,
Increases weapon repair rate by %s;
Increases Armor and structural resistance by %s;
Reduces flux dissipation rate by %s.

Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

Increases system recharge rate by up to %s, increasing with current flux level;

When the ship's system does not recharge, the system's max use is increased by %s ;

Also increase the ship's max CR by %s.

Built-in modular hullmod; cycle between alternatives by removing this hullmod.

During peak operation time, increases the ship's maneuverability by up to %s, increasing with the ship's total time in peak operation during this combat;
During peak operation time, significantly reduces damage to engines.
